<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - INSTALL - INPUT
        SHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1302007" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="7">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>To assemble the input shaft assembly, the mainshaft drive gear must be installed and timed.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Replace pilot bushing, if worn.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Apply Eaton lubricant #71215 or equivalent to the pilot bushing so that a film of lubricant covers
                    the entire internal surface of the bushing.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the snap ring in the I.D. of the main drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m9">Figure 229</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020m9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020m9" filename="../figg13/g13020m9.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 229. Install Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use toolmaker's dye and mark the main drive gear for timing purposes (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m9">Figure 229</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Mark any two (2) adjacent teeth on the drive gear. Repeat the procedure for the two
                    (2) adjacent teeth directly opposite the first set marked.
                </emph>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inside the case, mesh the lower countershaft drive gear marked tooth with either set of
                marked teeth on the main drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n0">Figure 230</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020n0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020n0" filename="../figg13/g13020n0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 230. Mesh Lower Countershaft Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">From the front, slide the input shaft into the main drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n0">Figure 230</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the drive gear spacer on the input shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n1">Figure 231</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020n1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020n1" filename="../figg13/g13020n1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 231. Drive Gear Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the bearing on the input shaft with the bearing external snap ring to the outside (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n1">Figure 231</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged-end driver and maul to seat the input shaft bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n2">Figure 232</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020n2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020n2" filename="../figg13/g13020n2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 232. Input Shaft Bearing Seated</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bearing retainer snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n3">Figure 233</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020n3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020n3" filename="../figg13/g13020n3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 233. Bearing Retainer Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Push the input shaft bearing back into the case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n4">Figure 234</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020n4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020n4" filename="../figg13/g13020n4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 234. Input Shaft Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gasket on the bearing cover mounting surface, making sure to align the gasket
                oil return hole with case oil return hole (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n4">Figure 234</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the front bearing cover, making sure to align the cover oil return hole with the
                case oil return hole (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n5">Figure 235</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020n5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020n5" filename="../figg13/g13020n5.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 235. Align Cover/Case Oil Return Hole</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the front bearing cover with six (6) bolts and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61
                N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
